==English==
===Adverb===
#(in British English the correct spelling is ''for ever'') For all time, for all eternity; for an [[infinite]] amount of time. 
:''I shall love you for ever.''
#(''colloquially'') for a very long time. 
:''We had to wait forever to get inside.''
#(''colloquially'') constantly or frequently.
:''You are forever nagging me.''

